column15: Planned, performed and managed vehicle operations functions and activities. Dispatched, operated and serviced motor vehicles such as general and special-purpose vehicles, base maintenance, and material-handling vehicles. Performed fleet management duties, accounted for vehicle fleet, issued driver licenses and conducted analyses. Planned, organized and directed vehicle transportation to support operational missions.

Piloted aircraft and commanded crew to accomplish airlift, training and other missions. Planned and prepared for missions. Reviewed mission tasking, intelligence and weather information. Supervised planning, preparation and filing of flight plan and crew briefing. Ensured aircraft was pre-flighted, inspected, loaded, equipped and manned for flight. Performed, supervised or directed navigation, in-flight refueling, and cargo and passenger delivery.

Piloted USAF bomber aircraft and commanded crew. Operated aircraft controls and equipment. Performed, supervised or directed navigation, in-flight refueling and weapons delivery. Conducted or supervised training of crew members. Ensured operational readiness of crew by conducting or supervising mission-specific training. Planned and prepared for missions. Reviewed mission tasking, intelligence and weather information. Supervised mission planning, preparation and filing of flight plan, and crew briefing.

Formulated test procedures and conducted tests to evaluate performance, reliability and suitability of aircraft and systems. Identified design and operational deficiencies and recommended improvements.

Aviator trained to engage in air-to-air, and often air-to-ground, combat while at the controls of a fighter aircraft. Underwent specialized technical training. Planned and prepared for missions. Reviewed mission tasking, intelligence and weather information. Supervised mission planning, preparation and filing of flight plan, and crew briefing. Ensured aircraft was pre-flighted, inspected, loaded, equipped and manned for missions that ensured safe return.
Monitored, evaluated and directed flying operations and training programs. Developed requirements for equipment and training. Prepared and coordinated budgets.

Piloted helicopter aircraft and commanded crews to accomplish combat, training and other missions. Planned and prepared for missions. Reviewed mission tasking, intelligence and weather information. Supervised mission planning and crew briefing. Ensured aircraft was pre-flighted, inspected, loaded, equipped and manned for missions. Conducted or supervised training of crew members. Operated aircraft controls and equipment.

Reviewed syllabus requirements, student progress and weather information. Piloted aircraft and commanded crew. Ensured optimum training opportunities and progress by conducting and supervising student training.
Piloted highly specialized aircraft designed specifically with intent to capture EW and aerial reconnaissance surveillance as well as search and rescue, training, and other missions.

Piloted special operations aircraft and commanded crews of special operations forces for worldwide deployment and assignment to regional unified commands to conduct unconventional warfare, direct action and special reconnaissance. Managed personnel recovery and counterterrorism operations.

Planned and prepared for activities. Ensured readiness of crew by conducting and supervising activity-specific training. Tankered aircraft and commanded crews to accomplish air refueling, airlift, training and other missions.

Navigator officer performed, conducted or directly supported flying operations, including combat, combat support and training missions. Inherently included were supervisory and staff functions such as inspection, contingency planning and policy formulation.

Performed duties of navigator, electronic warfare officer (EWO) or weapon systems officer (WSO) to accomplish combat, training and other assigned missions. Reviewed mission tasking, intelligence and weather information. Conducted or supervised training of crew members. Ensured operational readiness of crew by conducting or supervising mission- and activity-specific training.
Planned and conducted flight test programs. Managed research and tested and evaluated projects and programs. Identified design and operational deficiencies and recommended improvements.

Performed duties of weapon systems officer or electronic warfare officer to accomplish combat, training and other assigned missions. Navigated aircraft to accomplish assigned missions. Operated available navigation systems. Conducted or supervised training of crew members. Developed plans and policies, monitored operations, and advised commanders. Navigated aircraft. Participated in planning, preparation, crew briefing and filing of flight plans.
Monitored, evaluated and directed flying operations and training programs. Developed requirements for equipment and training. Prepared and coordinated budgets.
Reviewed syllabus requirements, student progress and weather information. Navigated aircraft. Ensured optimum training opportunities and progress by conducting and supervising student training.

Piloted specialized mission aircraft and commanded flight crews to accomplish reconnaissance, surveillance, search and rescue, electronic warfare, training, and other missions. Participated in planning, preparation, crew briefing and filing of flight plans. Ensured readiness of crew by conducting and supervising activity-specific training.

Performed duties of navigator, fire control officer (FCO) or electronic warfare officer (EWO) to accomplish special operations, training and other assigned missions. Navigated aircraft to accomplish assigned missions. Operated available navigation systems.

Performed duties of navigator in tanker aircraft to accomplish air refueling, training and other assigned missions. Participated in mission planning, preparation and filing of flight plans, and crew briefing. Ensured aircraft was pre-flighted, inspected, loaded, equipped and manned for missions. Navigated aircraft to accomplish assigned missions. Operated available navigation systems.
Commanded space shuttle missions. Assessed problems and implemented deviations from flight plans, procedures and personnel assignments in the interest of safety and mission accomplishment.

Developed plans, policies and procedures. Selected and employed surveillance, reporting and data link management systems. Interpreted directives into specific guidance and procedures for controller actions.
Coordinated, planned and conducted personnel recovery missions. Ensured safe, orderly and expeditious air traffic flow in and around the terminal area.

Managed day-to-day operations of facilities including radar approach control, ground controlled approach, radar final control, control tower and base operations. Provided staff supervision and technical assistance.

Built future plans, requirements, concepts, directives and exercises for operational employment of space and missile systems and facilities. Established organizational structure and determined personnel requirements.

Conducted information operations to analyze information vulnerability. Provided staff supervision and technical advice. Planned and coordinated use of intelligence resources, programming and budgeting.

Analyzed meteorological data and prepared forecasts. Integrated weather analyses and reports with radar and satellite imagery interpretations. Briefed aircrews and staff personnel on current and forecasted weather.
Provided foreign language competency and regional expertise essential to interaction with foreign organizations. Made recommendations on treaties, international agreements, policies and procedures.

Developed and created assumptions for the planning process that are responsive to doctrine and maximize the capabilities of the USAF. Programmed, presented and supported resource allocation according to the Planning, Programming and Budgeting System. Facilitated issue resolution to ensure timely completion.
Developed policy positions on international political problems. Made recommendations on treaties, international agreements, policies and procedures.

Executed planning process based on policies, directives and procedures. Developed assumptions upon which the planning process was constrained. Coordinated plans between staff agencies to ensure a coherent planning effort.

Led and trained personnel supporting aerospace equipment sustainment and operations. Managed maintenance and modification of aircraft and associated equipment. Administered aircraft maintenance programs.

Managed and trained personnel supporting aerospace equipment sustainment and operations. Administered aircraft and equipment maintenance programs. Directed staff activity and related supply inventory such as aircraft, missile, avionics, communications-electronics and munitions.

Scheduled, planned and operated maintenance of management information system (MIS), and collected, analyzed and presented data to maintenance organizations. Collaborated with organizations to include aircraft, missile, avionics, communications-electronics and other collaterals.

Oversaw and integrated the spectrum of logistics processes within the operational, acquisition and wholesale environments. Directed and managed the supply distribution logistics and management of needed inventory.

Led, managed and directed Security Forces personnel and deployments. Protected nuclear and conventional weapons systems and other resources. Directed air base defense resources including control and security of terrain inside and immediately adjacent to military installations. Included were weapons systems and resource security; anti-terrorism; law enforcement and investigations; military working-dog functions; air base defense; armament and equipment; training pass and registration; information, personnel and industrial security; and combat arms.

Directed, developed and implemented civil engineer (CE) force employment. Organized, trained and equipped contingency forces for conventional and nuclear, biological and chemical (NBC) attack operations, and other emergency situations. Directly involved programming, budgeting, project management, drafting, surveying, planning, feasibility studies, construction management, utilities operations, energy and environmental programs, land management, and real property accounting.

Supported joint and service communications and information requirements. Implemented and conducted communications and information unit operations. Conducted defensive operations. Managed communications-related plans. Supported force employment planning, execution and combat assessment. Conducted strategic planning. Developed and wrote Air Force, joint service, and combined communications and information plans, programs and policies. Coordinated plans to ensure coherent planning efforts.

Directed, supervised and administered appropriated and nonappropriated fund food facilities, temporary lodging facilities, and health, fitness and recreation programs and facilities. Directed child development, protocol and leisure functions. Trained and supervised search-and-recovery teams. Oversaw training and advising of unit fitness managers in fitness evaluation procedures, and conducted fitness improvement training programs and oversight of food service, lodging, fitness, mortuary and recreation.

Provided professional musical products and services for official military, recruiting and community relations events, as well as government activities such as ceremonies, formations and parades. Provided an essential element in maintaining troop morale, retention and recruiting efforts. Performed at a level of comparable commercial musicians.

Planned, recruited, budgeted, trained, executed and evaluated effectiveness of public affairs programs. Directed full-time staff in print, broadcast, radio, digital and community relations. Provided public affairs advice, counsel and support for commanders and senior staff people.

Planned programs for health and wellness/fitness, education, welfare and family support. Provided leadership necessary to ensure comprehensive family support programs. Included were food service (dining facilities, flight kitchens and other food service facilities); transient housing (visiting quarters and temporary lodging facilities); mortuary affairs (search and recovery, inspection of human remains, briefing next of kin, military honors, honor guard management, and personal property program); and recreation activities. Oversaw budget requirements of all mission support areas.

Managed personnel activities and functions, including personnel action requests; source documents; unit, field and master personnel records; and Commander's Support Staff (CSS) tasks. Supervised and performed human resources functions. Recorded information in unit, field and PDS records. Prepared and maintained personnel records, orders and personnel action requests. Prepared and processed documentation for administration of quality control programs.

Field encompasses core competencies in personnel requirements determination, organization structure, program allocation and control, and performance management. Oversaw functions of policy planning, program formulating, directing management engineering, performance improvement and manpower activities. Immediate supervisory and technical responsibilities for developing and maintaining manpower standards and directing manpower and organization management policies. Advised leadership on manpower management and continuous improvement initiatives and activities.

Managed health services activities, including human resources, patient administration, fiscal management and medical facility management. Directed the hospital accreditation program and management improvement studies.

Planned, coordinated, controlled, directed and evaluated PT activities. Determined and implemented policies and procedures pertaining to PT programs and activities. Determined requirements for PT services including personnel, equipment, supplies and continuing education. Established professional care standards, and established and appraised performance levels of subordinates.

Examined eyes and vision. Examined eyes for presence of defects or visual anomalies that could be corrected, remedied or relieved by using lenses, prisms, orthopedics, contact lenses or other ophthalmic devices. Performed external and internal examination of eyes and referred pathology to medical specialties.

Provided examination, diagnosis, treatment, prevention and care of conditions and functions of the human foot. Planned, administered and recorded progress of prescribed courses of treatment of the foot and related structures. Accomplished therapeutic procedures. Consulted with other practitioners, as appropriate, for further care, diagnosis and treatment planning. Instructed patients in prescribed therapeutic procedures. Prescribed medication within limitations of podiatric practice.

Provided medical care under the supervision of a physician. Analyzed and interpreted data, formulated problem lists, and established plans for solution of clinical problems. Counseled patients on numerous health matters.

Tested, diagnosed, treated and cared for those with speech and hearing problems.  Those who cannot hear are often unable to speak. Problem was discerned, and treatment with the health care team was begun with other specialist(s).
Administered clinical psychology programs. Supervised mental health personnel and recommended policies pertaining to their training and management. Performed mental health evaluations and therapy.
Managed and provided social service in mental health, medical, correctional and child advocacy settings. Developed social work staff training programs.

Formulated and implemented policies and procedures for occupational therapy programs. Performed evaluation procedures, gave therapeutic guidance and instruction, and reported patient responses and progress.

Managed all functions of USAF aerospace physiological training units or flights. Planned and directed all activities of personnel and programs required to train aircrews and others in the physiological hazards and human factor problems of flying operations. Instructed personnel such as trainee flight surgeons, flight nurses, observers and aircrew in aerospace physiology, human factors and related subjects. Instructed trainees in such subjects as physics of atmosphere, physiology of respiration, accelerative forces, physiology of blood and circulation, effects of temperature, physiological effects of altitude, self-imposed stresses, aviation human factors, circadian rhythm, and night vision.

Planned, administered and managed multidisciplinary professional programs and activities in the broad area of biomedical sciences, in general simply known as medical research, basic research, applied research or translational research conducted to aid and support the body of knowledge in the field of medicine. Directed and formulated biomedical sciences programs. Developed, evaluated and interpreted policies in the biomedical sciences. Managed professional programs for technical training, research, clinical practice and operational support.

Managed nutritional medicine dietary regimen recently called "the pyramid." Formulated and implemented policies and procedures for organization and operation of nutritional medicine. Determined medical food service requirements for personnel and equipment. Inspected and evaluated food preparation and service to patients and duty personnel for conformance with dietetic standards.

Completed and supervised bioenvironmental engineering programs. Performed risk assessment surveys and evaluated systems, installations, facilities and planning documents for chemical, physical and biological stress factors.
Developed, planned and implemented military public health activities. Conducted preventive medicine and communicable disease control, occupational health, food safety and disaster response programs.

Developed medical entomologic portion of training programs for preventive medicine activities. Instructed technicians in collection, handling, identification, prevention and control of disease-associated arthropods, other noxious or toxic animals, and poisonous plants. Advised surgeons at all levels of military capabilities and programs for prevention or control of anthropod and other animal-associated epidemics. Wrote and maintained medical entomologic regulations and forms. Developed and administered medical pest management programs focused upon insects and arthropods that impact human health.

Managed and directed all pharmacy operations, including procurement, storage, manufacture, distribution, control and evaluation of drugs. Formulated specifications for the quality and source of all drugs procured by the pharmacy. Supervised filling, labeling and dispensing of all drug orders. Inspected stock supplies of drugs on all services; maintained an approved stock of antidotes and other emergency drugs. Directed operation of the intravenous admixture program. Implemented unit dose drug distribution systems. Maintained patient drug profiles for inpatients as well as outpatients when feasible. Provided consultative services.

Served as chief of Laboratory Services or as chief of one or more areas of Laboratory Services. Supervised the management of reference data for members of the medical provider staff. Maintained records and reports on laboratory operations necessary to provide workload accountability. Served on professional, technical, consultant and advisory committees to improve working relationships with other staff members. Taught and instructed medical and related personnel in both technical and interpretive aspects for a variety of laboratory sciences.

Managed independent and collaborative research using animals. Researched zoonosis to learn its incidence and prevent its spread to humans and other animals. Directed personnel engaged in care and treatment of animals.

Developed measures to control radiological hazards; monitored personnel and facilities to ensure permissible limits of health hazards were met. Coordinated all health physics activities, and conducted research and development. Conducted hospital medical physics program for radiotherapy, nuclear medicine and diagnostic services.

Administered medical service policies. Planned and administered medical services at facilities, including maintenance of health standards, training and use of personnel. Coordinated medical service programs. Coordinated health service and patient care with military and civilian medical treatment facilities.
Diagnosed diseases by performing necropsies and pathological examinations of body tissues. Analyzed case histories and prepared tissues for microscopic examination. Wrote diagnostic reports.

Examined, diagnosed and treated illnesses and injuries in the acute care setting. Provided immediate diagnoses and resuscitation care for life-threatening conditions. Directed the provision of such care in prehospital settings.

Examined patients, formulated differential diagnostic plans and ordered required testing. Interpreted examination findings and implemented treatment plans. Determined need for consultation and liaised with other specialists.

Examined, diagnosed and treated diseases and injuries. Examined patients and determined x-ray examinations and clinical laboratory tests required. Interpreted test results and evaluated examination findings.
Used radionuclides in diagnostic imaging and the treatment of disease. Reviewed requests for nuclear imaging and therapeutic procedures. Instructed and directed nuclear medicine technologists.

Evaluated, diagnosed and treated genetic diseases. Examined patients, determined need for laboratory testing and interpreted findings. Counseled patients and parents on recurrence risks and availability of prenatal diagnoses.

Examined, diagnosed and treated diseases and injuries of infants and children extending into young adulthood. Determined patient need for x-ray examinations and clinical laboratory tests. Interpreted findings and results.
Diagnosed and treated diseases. Prepared and reviewed case histories and clinical records. Performed and interpreted diagnostic procedures including x-ray examinations and clinical laboratory tests.
Examined, diagnosed and treated neurological diseases and disorders. Determined patient needs for clinical laboratory tests and interpreted examination findings and test results.
Examined, evaluated, diagnosed and treated psychiatric disorders. Prescribed and evaluated effectiveness of a wide range of therapeutic measures. Directed mental health clinics.

Managed radiological services. Made and interpreted diagnostic images. Recommended and performed special imaging procedures, including fluoroscopy, tomography, angiography, nuclear imaging, ultrasound, and computed tomography, MRI and MRA, with limitations of available resources and expertise.
Diagnosed and treated skin diseases. Examined patients, performed biopsies and determined requirements for clinical laboratory tests. Interpreted test results and evaluated examination findings.

Managed and formulated plans and procedures for management of radiotherapy services. Key member of medical team in treatment of oncology patients. Active in the multidisciplinary management of cancer patients. Evaluated patients to determine suitability for radiation therapy.

Examined, diagnosed and treated diseases and injuries by surgical and nonsurgical means. Prepared and reviewed case histories. Prescribed treatments including drugs, physical therapy, dietary regimens and surgical procedures.
Examined, diagnosed and treated allergic diseases. Prescribed specific medications, diets and immunotherapy. Managed allergy services.

Administered general and local anesthetics. Determined anesthetics to be used considering such factors as patient conditions and operations to be performed. Coordinated administration of anesthetics with surgeons during operations.

Examined and treated diseases and musculoskeletal system injuries. Determined x-ray examinations and clinical laboratory tests required and evaluated findings. Determined procedures for preoperative and postoperative care.

Examined, diagnosed and treated eye diseases and injuries. Provided care in inpatient and outpatient settings. Assessed visual and refractive status, measured intraocular pressure and examined the eye and adnexa.

Managed obstetrical and gynecological services. Regarded as expert in primary care of women. Formulated plans and procedures for obstetrical and gynecological services. Scheduled operation of obstetrical and gynecological services with other medical activities. Instructed interns and student residents in obstetrical and gynecological procedures. Served as consultant on obstetrics and gynecology.

Examined, diagnosed and treated head and neck injuries and disorders. Interpreted and evaluated x-ray examination and clinical laboratory test findings. Determined procedures for preoperative and postoperative care.

Examined, diagnosed and treated disabilities. Prescribed electrotherapy, ultrasonography, heat and cold therapy, hydrotherapy, debridement, diathermy, radiation, and orthotic and prosthetic applications.

Examined, diagnosed and treated diseases and injuries by surgical means. Determined procedures for preoperative and postoperative care, such as administering sedatives, prescribing diets and preparing operative area of patient.

Examined, diagnosed and treated, by surgical means, genitourinary tract injuries and disorders. Examined patients and determined x-ray examinations and laboratory tests required. Interpreted test results and findings.

Planned, initiated and directed execution of nursing activities. Evaluated qualifications and managed nursing personnel. Planned and directed assignment and training of professional and nonprofessional nursing personnel.

Planned and prepared for aeromedical evacuation missions. Provided for in-flight management and nursing care for all types of patients. Informed appropriate personnel of changes in patients' conditions.

Rendered comprehensive care to women from menarche through menopause. Evaluated prenatal patient conditions and formulated care plans. Consulted primary obstetrician and co-managed comprehensive care for high-risk patients.

Monitored and supervised management of patient perioperative experiences. Advised anesthesiologists and appropriate physicians of adverse reactions necessitating medical decisions. Provided postoperative recovery care.

Assessed health and needs of individuals and populations. Used data to determine nursing needs of individual patients and populations, including abnormal physiological findings, risk factors and nursing diagnoses.

Worked with individuals, families, groups and communities to assess mental health needs, develop diagnoses and plans, and implement and evaluate nursing care. Monitored patients undergoing detoxification from alcohol and drugs.

Provided professional nursing care to patients undergoing surgery. Established and utilized a checklist to monitor the physical plan of the operating room and equipment for conformity to all standards.

Examined, diagnosed and treated irregularities and malocclusion of teeth and malrelation of jaws. Evaluated findings and determined types of appliances to move and guide teeth and jaws into proper positions and relationships.

Examined and diagnosed pathologic conditions of oral and other proximate tissues and structures. Directed oral and maxillofacial pathology service. Formulated and implemented procedures for operation of oral and maxillofacial pathology service. Determined personnel required to accomplish diagnostic tests and examination. Planned work schedules for personnel. Coordinated oral and maxillofacial pathology service with other dental and medical services.
Examined, diagnosed and treated dental pulp diseases and periapical tissues of teeth. Evaluated findings and prescribed treatment to prevent teeth loss. Performed therapeutic and surgical procedures.

Diagnosed and treated diseases, abnormalities, injuries and dysfunctional disorders of the oral cavity and its associated structures. Examined patients and interpreted radiographs and diagnostic tests to determine treatments.

Diagnosed and treated diseases of investing hard and soft tissues of teeth. Prescribed and administered medications in treatment of diseases and infection of the oral cavity. Instructed patients on oral hygiene and preventive measures.

Diagnosed and treated diseases, abnormalities, injuries and dysfunctional disorders of the oral cavity and its associated structures in children. Provided behavior management techniques. Performed surgeries and treatments on children.
Examined and diagnosed disabilities caused by loss of teeth and supporting structures. Formulated and executed treatment plans for construction of corrective prostheses.

Diagnosed and treated abnormalities and injuries of oral and maxillofacial structures. Performed oral surgical operations to remove infected, impacted and malposed teeth. Prepared jaws for prosthodontic appliances.
Liaised with federal, state and local agencies in matters related to aerospace medicine, preventive medicine and occupational medicine. Established medical standards for flying personnel.
Determined frequency and scope of occupational medicine exams required by federal regulations. Conducted periodic health exams. Advised medical and dental staff on treatment of flying personnel.

Provided continuing comprehensive health maintenance and medical care to personnel, dependents and retirees. Directed outpatient and inpatient care and service. Examined personnel to determine fitness for flying and special duties.
Developed policies and procedures and prepared directives governing flight, preventive and occupational medicine. Liaised with government agencies in matters related to aerospace medicine.

Directed health education and control measures for preventable diseases and injuries. Determined adequacy of living and working environments. Developed and implemented research projects to control and prevent diseases.
Formulated legal policies. Advised and developed plans for operation and implementation of federal statutes and executive orders. Prepared and rendered legal advice and opinions.

Conducted worship services, liturgies and rites. Provided counseling, pastoral care, visitation, religious education, morale programs, spiritual renewal, lay leadership programs and humanitarian outreach opportunities.

Conducted and managed research. Planned research projects, determined theoretical aspects of problems and selected methods of approach. Developed new concepts, methods and techniques to solve scientific problems.

Performed systems planning activities associated with design, development, manufacturing, sustainment and modification of systems to satisfy customer requirements. Identified and transitioned new technologies.

Managed defense acquisition programs covering every aspect of the acquisition/procurement process, including integrating engineering, program control, test and deployment, configuration management, production and manufacturing, quality assurance, and logistics support. Managed cost, schedules, performance and supportability of programs or support activities.

Coordinated contracting activities. Analyzed purchase requests and technical documents for suitability and determined the proper contracting method and contract type. Prepared and distributed solicitations and evaluated offers.

Conducted audit activities. Determined compliance with policies, directives, procedures and standards of performance. Evaluated management systems and internal controls to determine their adequacy and effectiveness.

Planned and developed techniques and established internal controls to manage financial services and analysis operations. Determined organizational structure, training needs and security requirements for safeguarding assets.
Organized and supervised cost activities and programs. Established procedures and techniques for analyzing and evaluating performance against standards and developing and validating data sources.

Formulated special investigations policy governing programs in counterintelligence, criminal, fraud and technical services areas. Established investigative work loads based on complexity of cases and capability of units.

Coordinated training and instructional programs at the U.S. Air Force Academy. Monitored unit performance in all athletic programs, including intramural and recreational sports and physical fitness programs.
Led flight pilot training. Motivated students to become professional career pilots. Developed training policies involving discipline, military training, administration and academic progress.
Developed course syllabi, training project outlines, and daily and weekly lesson plans. Prepared assignments, laboratory exercises, demonstrations and training aids to supplement course outline.
Directed instruction organization and preparation. Established education and training objectives. Managed development of course syllabi, educational project outlines and lesson plans.

Searched and recruited appropriate candidates, and inspired, engaged and recruited the brightest, most competitive and diverse men and women for service in America's Air Force. Acquired a steady flow of new candidates and provided them with difficult, highly technical training that equipped them with the skills to sustain the combat capability of the USAF. Recruited approximately 1,000 officers and 27,000 enlisted members each year.
Planned, directed and conducted historical research projects. Developed procedures to prepare studies. Assured completeness and accuracy in research as well as clarity and relevance in writing.

Conducted full honor arrival ceremonies conducted at the White House for the President and foreign heads of state. Determined funds needed to support unit activities and prepared budget justification.

Created procedures for improving operations. Developed, conducted and evaluated training plans and training programs. Developed operational concepts; translated support missions into force requirements. Established procedures and monitored plans and programs to implement joint and combined operations. Reported results to senior leadership.

Operated and monitored voice and electronic communication systems. Maintained and ensured communications systems integrity and readiness status. Monitored installation upgrades and communication facility modifications.

Planned, directed, conducted and monitored IG activities. Operated and managed the Office of the Inspector General. Responsible for overall operation, administration and management of IG programs. Developed, established and controlled methods and procedures to implement IG policies and programs. Reviewed and evaluated IG programs and activities.

Performed primary duty as an aide-de-camp for the Secretary of the Air Force, Chief of Staff of the Air Force, Vice Chief of Staff of the Air Force or commanders with rank of O-8 through O-10. Expert and current knowledge of military customs and courtesies, protocols, USAF organization, missions, history, and policies were mandatory. Outstanding military bearing and appearance. Demonstrated ability to organize and complete complex tasks and projects attested to in performance reports or commander's recommendation, or both. Ability and willingness for extensive travel, foreign and domestic.
Directly supported the commander by handling all aspects of visits, conferences, tours and social functions. Arranged travel for VIPs. Prepared their itineraries.
Conducted interviews to determine factors that could boost morale and productivity. Provided information and guidance on career decisions. Developed publicity programs.

Received and maintained records of telephone calls, made appointments, and received guests and visitors. Assisted in planning, preparing, arranging and conducting official social functions and activities.

Planned, organized and directed basic and initial training. Planned and organized training requirements. Determined requirements for facilities, space, equipment, visual aids and supplies to support training requirements, and monitored the training program to ensure effective use of support items. Inspected and evaluated training activities, results and facilities.

Planned, organized and directed educational instruction. Established and conducted student entry briefings. Motivated personnel to develop proper attitudes, effective human relations and social skills for improving relations.

Provided instruction and evaluated training. Advised management on a wide range of topics including the health, discipline, mentoring, well-being, training, professional development and recognition of all assigned students.

Provided leadership and management support for FSC operations. Served as the principal military advisor to the staff and as the liaison to the community. Provided military and civilian families assistance and support during times of local or national emergency or disasters, mobilization, deployment, separation, or evacuation. Intermediary with Red Cross, FEMA and other like organizations.

Collected and reported intelligence information obtained from human sources in response to requirements. Assessed, debriefed and interrogated sources in English and foreign languages. Translated written material and interpreted conversation from one language to another. Translated from one language to another and captured the intent of idiomatic expressions.

Participated in planning, coordinating, collecting, evaluating and interpreting data, and writing reports detailing the results of research or applied engineering investigations. Explored and tested new ideas.

Principal advisor to the commander on all issues related to the enlisted force. Exercised general supervision over assigned enlisted personnel. Provided a mission-ready team to execute operations. Exercised the necessary leadership to provide an able workforce for operations.

Participated in arrival and departure ceremonies for the President, foreign heads of state, and other national or international dignitaries. Coordinated on matters pertaining to ceremonies and protocol.

Supervised correctional custody programs. Determined requirements for personnel, facilities, space, equipment and supplies to support incarceration requirements of population. Monitored the program to ensure effective use of support items.
Separated and sorted mail into proper classes and destination or off-load points. Provided security for registered mail at commercial terminals. Recorded accountable mail on receipts before delivery.

Safeguarded and delivered sensitive material. Verified each item by identification number when receipting for or delivering material. Maintained constant surveillance over material in custody on the courier route.

Maintained reporting requirements and budget and fiscal data. Provided feedback to others on the quantity and quality of their information reporting. Maintained statistics for information reporting purposes.

Searched the market for appropriate candidates, and inspired, engaged and recruited the brightest men and women for the USAF. Developed and managed a pipeline of new candidates for rigorous, highly technical training that equipped them with the skills to sustain the combat capability of the USAF. Team recruited approximately 1,000 officers and 27,000 enlisted members each year.

Managed normal and emergency procedures and inspections on Missile Alert Facility (MAF) equipment. Inspected water treatment systems, power production systems, lighting and temperature controls, and other support systems required for daily operation. Provided oversight of water treatment system and diesel generator tests and adjustments. Supervised daily activities at MAF.

Operated infrared and low-light-level television (LLLTV) sensor systems, illuminator equipment, and allied components; performed aircrew functions. Assisted mission planning by assembling target information, and locating forces and hostile defense locations. Prepared mission and maintenance reports for leadership.

Directed and conducted military education programs for airmen, noncommissioned officers (NCOs) and civilians. Served as management consultant resource. Created and revised curriculum materials and monitored program effectiveness. Planned and organized phases of education, student flow and class schedules.
Advised personnel on contracting related issues. Obtained and analyzed data on marketing trends, supply sources and trade information. Prepared memoranda, justifications and approvals.

Performed, supervised, managed and directed financial management activities throughout the U.S. and abroad. Provided customer service. Maintained financial records for pay and travel transactions. Maintained accounting records and prepared reports. Served as financial advisor to commanders and resource managers. Prepared budgets and executed financial plans. Performed audits and implemented fraud prevention measures. Scheduled, prepared, verified and submitted financial accounting reports.

Performed paraprofessional and legal research functions under the supervision of a judge advocate in connection with civil law, military justice and claims activities. Supervised administration of legal services and court reporting activities. Provided administrative and litigation support in processing and execution of all judicial matters.

Managed and implemented support of religious observances. Prepared and maintained religious accouterments, facilities and equipment. Organized, trained, supervised and coordinated with laity to support chapel-based ministry.
Analyzed performance and isolated malfunctioning avionics test and support equipment. Inspected, maintained, programmed and calibrated avionics equipment, support equipment and aircraft components.

column14: A-10, F-15 and U-2 Avionics Systems
column15: Interpreted equipment operation to isolate systems malfunctions. Traced data flow and wiring diagrams. Removed, installed, aligned and checked integrated avionics systems.

column14: F-16, F-117, RQ-1 and CV-22 Avionics Systems
column15: Removed and installed system components. Performed and supervised alignment, calibration and boresight of avionic systems. Inspected, analyzed and evaluated avionic systems to determine operational status.
Performed end-of-runway, post-flight, pre-flight, thru-flight and phase aircraft inspections. Advised on problems maintaining, servicing and inspecting aircraft and related aerospace equipment.

Troubleshot and maintained aircraft structures, systems, components and support equipment. Tested repaired components using mockups and test equipment. Adjusted, aligned, rigged and calibrated aircraft systems.

Troubleshot, inspected, repaired and serviced aircraft, systems and related equipment. Inspected and functionally checked helicopter structures and systems. Checked installed components for proper operation.
Operated and maintained avionics systems. Removed, installed, checked and repaired avionics systems and line replaceable units. Modified avionics systems according to technical publications.

Planned, organized and directed aerospace propulsion maintenance activities. Troubleshot and determined repair procedures on aircraft engines. Inspected, certified and approved completed maintenance actions.

Inspected, tested and operated aerospace ground equipment to determine serviceability and proper operation. Diagnosed mechanical and electronic circuitry malfunctions and tested equipment and technical publications.
Advised on and solved installation, maintenance and repair problems. Diagnosed malfunctions and recommended corrective action. Implemented maintenance and safety policies for egress systems.

Supervised, inspected and evaluated aircraft fuel systems maintenance activities. Performed maintenance on aircraft fuel tanks and cells. Prepared aircraft surfaces and applied sealants, adhesives and associated chemicals.
Performed maintenance on aircraft hydraulic systems. Troubleshot, removed, repaired, overhauled, replaced, adjusted and tested malfunctioning components. Performed system operational checks.

Maintained, inspected and troubleshot aircraft electrical and environmental systems, subsystems and components. Interpreted inspection findings and determined corrective actions. Ensured compliance with technical standards.

Designed, manufactured and modified special precision tools, gauges, dies and fixtures to facilitate metal working operations. Performed metals technology shop calculations. Checked components for wear tolerances.

Members of the Naval Criminal Investigative Service (NCIS) team who perform the full spectrum of criminal investigative duties prescribed for and are operationally assigned to the NClS. Special function is administering polygraph examinations.

Performed routine inspections, transported prisoners and processed personnel for confinement and release. Managed prisoner funds and personal property. Observed and reported meaningful changes in prisoner behavior.

Provided recommendations on clemency, parole and/or restoration to duty requests. Interpreted, applied and reviewed policies, regulations and directives.

Researched, prepared and typed general correspondence, forms, reports, wills, powers of attorney and other documents dealing with legal matters. Checked all completed work for typographical accuracy. Maintained office correspondence.
